#Outputs$Outputs
    Outputs are those points which output a signal from the T3000. They correspond directly with the physical outputs wired to the panel. Outputs may be either digital (only 2 states, on/off) or analog (infinite states, 0-10 Volts). Each T3000 has the capacity to handle 128 outputs with expansion capabilities for a further 128 outputs. 
    Output setup fields: 
a)  Full_label
    A 20 character descriptor which is usually used to associate a give point with the
physical location. 

b)  A/m 
    When in auto the output will accept commands from Control Basic. When in manual the
output will  remain at a fixed value. To change from auto to manual or vice versa simply
highlight the field and press " 

c)  Value 
    This field contains the value of the output point which may be digital or analog
depending on the range selected. To toggle a digital value highlight the field and press
ENTER. To change an analog value highlight the field and press ENTER followed by
the new value and ENTER. Note that it is only practical to change an input value when
the point is in manual. 

d)  Units 
    The scale with which the Value is to be read 
    To set the range highlight the field, press ENTER, and select either Analog, Digital or Custom Digital. Then enter the desired range number. 
e)  Range
    The range field is set to match the sensor that is connected to the input. 
    To set the range highlight the field, press ENTER, and select either Analog, Digital or Custom Digital. Then enter the desired range number. 

f)  0% 
    When the range selected is 0-100% or 0-100 % open, "Low" sets the output voltage when the value is 0.00%. Note that when the value is 1% the voltage output will be either 0V (if Low is less than High) or 12V (if Low is greater than High). This is to ensure that the output transducer is driven fully to the 0% position. 

g)  100% 
    When the range selected is 0-100% or 0-100 % open, "High" sets the output voltage when the value is 100%. Note that when the value is 101.0 % the voltage output will be either 12V (if High" is greater than "Low") or 0V (if "High" is less than "Low"). This is to ensure that the output transducer is driven fully to the 100% position. 

h)  D (Decommissioned) 
    This field is a flag indicating if the point has been taken out of service. The normal indicator is a dash (-), if decommissioned this field will have a Y (Yes) in it. If a point is decommissioned it will be flagged as such when displayed in Control Groups. 

i)  Label 
    An 8 character descriptor. 
